<subSubSection id="A8D0653DFFFFFF995889F92EFBB36608" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E07536B6FFFFFF995889F92EFBB36608" blockId="50.[151,1437,1446,1905]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FFFFFF995912F92EFE4467C4" author="Rondani, C." box="[268,503,1699,1725]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b: 89)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FFFFFF995A6AF92EFCCA67C4" box="[628,889,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FFFFFF995A6AF92EFCC767C4" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1848" box="[628,884,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Blepharepium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridum">Blepharepium luridum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FFFFFF995CD1F92EFA9667C4" box="[1231,1317,1699,1725]" family="Number" pageId="50" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the sex of the specimens, but giving a single measurement of length, from material collected in South America by V. Ghiliani and received from G. Mussino. 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FFFFFF995A97F966FCF0667C" author="Costa, A." box="[649,835,1770,1797]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="13 - 48" refId="ref348459" refString="Costa, A. (1866) Acquisti fatti durante l'anno 1863. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della Regia Universita di Napoli, 3, 13 - 48." type="journal article" year="1866">Costa (1866: 35)</bibRefCitation>
listed a single MZUN specimen numbered “780”. We also found 
<specimenCount id="F6CCFD3FFFFFFF995959F882FE7D6650" box="[327,462,1807,1833]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
in this study. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FFFFFF995AFFF882FC7E6653" author="Rondani, C." box="[737,973,1807,1834]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b: 63)</bibRefCitation>
only gave the type locality as “ 
<collectingCountry id="98DD7626FFFFFF995D29F882FA3E6650" box="[1335,1421,1807,1833]" name="Brazil" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Brasile</collectingCountry>
”, 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FFFFFF9958D9F8BEFE086634" author="Papavero, N." box="[199,443,1843,1869]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref362581" refString="Papavero, N. (1973) Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology, with special reference to collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. 2. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paolo, Sao Paolo, pp. 217 - 446." type="book" year="1973">Papavero (1973: 343)</bibRefCitation>
gave a more accurate type locality based on a note in 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FFFFFF995C3EF8BEFB7B6634" author="Spinola, M." box="[1056,1224,1842,1869]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="19 - 94" refId="ref374743" refString="Spinola, M. (1853) Compte rendu des hymenopteres inedits provenants du voyage entomologique de M. Ghiliani dans le Para en 1846. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, Series 2, 13, 19 - 94." type="journal article" year="1853">Spinola (1853)</bibRefCitation>
that said all specimens collected by Ghiliani in 1846 were collected in Belem, Pará, 
<collectingCountry id="98DD7626FFFFFF995BAAF8DAFC4F6608" box="[948,1020,1879,1905]" name="Brazil" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
